(3) After the view (if any) of the body and the completion of the evidence, the coroner shall give his finding and certify it by an inquisition in writing in Form 5 in the Schedule, showing such of the matters set forth in subsection (1) as have been proved at the inquest, and, where the inquest concerns the death of a person executed in pursuance of a death warrant, the verdict and inquisition shall include a finding as to whether the death was instantaneous and the person executed was the person named in the said warrant.
